          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Safe Drugs Act</b></p> <p>This bill authorizes the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) to order the mandatory recall of any drug when the FDA determines that there is a reasonable probability that the drug would cause serious adverse health consequences or death. </p> <p>Currently, the FDA may order a mandatory recall under such circumstances only with respect to a controlled substance.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2020-08-06T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
